== Sheila Chisholm ==

Some refs I've been able to find re her affair with George: ''[https://books.google.com.au/books?id=PGAsmlQ9MksC&pg=PT134&dq=sheila+chisholm&hl=en&sa=X&ei=JVUEVZLYLYnv8gXJ7YCwAg&ved=0CD0Q6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=sheila%20chisholm&f=false The King Maker]'', ''[https://books.google.com.au/books?id=_uq-EI6MmL4C&pg=PA165&dq=sheila+chisholm&hl=en&sa=X&ei=JVUEVZLYLYnv8gXJ7YCwAg&ved=0CDcQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=sheila%20chisholm&f=false Charles & Camilla]'', ''[https://books.google.com.au/books?id=2bltAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA375&dq=sheila+chisholm&hl=en&sa=X&ei=JVUEVZLYLYnv8gXJ7YCwAg&ved=0CF4Q6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q=sheila%20chisholm&f=false We Danced All Night: A Social History of Britain Between the Wars]'', ''[https://books.google.com.au/books?id=r1BIQvLwv5sC&pg=PT150&dq=sheila+chisholm&hl=en&sa=X&ei=JVUEVZLYLYnv8gXJ7YCwAg&ved=0CE0Q6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=sheila%20chisholm&f=false Queen Elizabeth: The Queen Mother]''. It seems that George's dukedom hinged on his leaving Sheila, and that their affair was to be kept secret, which might explain the lack of coverage. Sheila seems to have understood this. One article [http://www.scotsman.com/news/remarkable-journey-of-margaret-sheila-mackellar-1-3290000 reads]: "She was, however, extremely discreet. Her memoirs say very little about Prince Albert, for instance, the man who was to become king following his brother Edward’s abdication and with whom she almost certainly had a long-running affair." [http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/02/19/article-2557831-1B3716E600000578-300_233x423.jpg Here] she is pictured with George and Edward. [http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-9ZLDtOoJbhw/UxgUa01EMnI/AAAAAAAAIKA/_-zgb5UnfQ4/s1600/SheilaChisholm4Dos.jpg Another pic], this one of "The 4 Do's". - [[User:HappyWaldo|HappyWaldo]] ([[User talk:HappyWaldo|talk]]) 16:17, 14 March 2015 (UTC)
:The sources, which include George's own letters, are not at issue. [[User:DrKay|DrKay]] ([[User talk:DrKay|talk]]) 16:28, 14 March 2015 (UTC)
There is absolutely nothing in this article whatsoever about "Shelia Chisholm," whomever she was nor Evelyn Laye, said to be George's lifelong love. Where on earth do you people get this information from?[[Special:Contributions/66.67.32.161|66.67.32.161]] ([[User talk:66.67.32.161|talk]]) 20:24, 28 March 2015 (UTC)

== Name ==

Albert Frederick Arthur George or Albert Frederick Arthur George Windsor? --[[User:Guy Macon|Guy Macon]] ([[User talk:Guy Macon|talk]]) 06:03, 24 July 2015 (UTC)

He was only ever a Prince (of the United Kingdom) or King-and therefore had no need of a surname. More to the point; 'Windsor' wasn't adopted as a surname for the male-line descendants of Queen Victoria until 1917.[[User:JWULTRABLIZZARD|JWULTRABLIZZARD]] ([[User talk:JWULTRABLIZZARD|talk]]) 13:40, 13 October 2015 (UTC)

